Name: Nowruz (Persian New Year)
Description: Nowruz, celebrated on March 21, marks the Persian New Year. It signifies the first day of spring and includes traditions rooted in Persian culture, history, and renewal.
PlacesToVisit: Kabul: Bagh-e Babur, Karte Se, Shahr-e-naw.

Name: Independence Day
Description: Afghanistan's Independence Day, celebrated on August 19, commemorates the Treaty of Rawalpindi in 1919, which gave Afghanistan full autonomy from British influence.
PlacesToVisit: Kabul: Independence Monument, Darul Aman Palace.

Name: E_id al-Fitr
Description: E_id al-Fitr marks the end of Ramadan, the holy month of fasting. It is celebrated with communal prayers, feasts, and charity.

Name: E_id al-Adha
Description: E_id al-Adha, also known as the Feast of Sacrifice, is celebrated by Muslims worldw_ide with prayers and the sacrifice of animals to commemorate Prophet Ibrahim's willingness to sacrifice his son.

Name: Ashura
Description: Ashura, observed on the 10th day of Muharram, is a day of mourning for Shia Muslims to commemorate the martyrdom of Imam Hussein at the Battle of Karbala.
